You are building a production-style portfolio project called MedDataGuard.

Project:
MedDataGuard — Medical Computer Vision Dataset QA, Leakage, and Drift Auditor

Goal:
Build a deployment-ready full-stack tool that scans image-segmentation datasets before model training and detects dataset-quality, annotation-quality, train/test leakage, class imbalance, image-quality, and domain-shift risks.

This is a local-first research/portfolio prototype. It is NOT a medical device, NOT a clinical validation system, and NOT intended for medical decision-making.

Core positioning:
Medical CV models can look good in offline evaluation while being unreliable because of bad data splits, duplicate frames, annotation issues, corrupted masks, class imbalance, or domain shift. MedDataGuard helps ML engineers inspect these risks before training or deployment.

Primary use case:
A medical AI engineer points MedDataGuard at a segmentation dataset containing image files, mask files, and optional split/metadata files. The system scans the dataset, flags issues, ranks risks, visualizes suspicious samples, and exports a reproducible audit report.

Target dataset compatibility:
- CholecSeg8k-style image/mask segmentation datasets
- Generic 2D image segmentation datasets
- Any dataset with:
  - image folder
  - mask folder
  - optional metadata.csv
  - optional train/val/test split files

Do not hard-code CholecSeg8k only. Make the scanner generic, but include a CholecSeg8k-friendly setup path.

